{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1101,"text":"What you have here"},{"time":2651,"text":"is an electronic cigarette."},{"time":6837,"text":"It's something that, since it was\ninvented a year or two ago,"},{"time":10080,"text":"has given me untold happiness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11575,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":12780,"text":"A little bit of it,\nI think, is the nicotine,"},{"time":15239,"text":"but there's something\nmuch bigger than that;"},{"time":17473,"text":"which is, ever since, in the UK,\nthey banned smoking in public places,"},{"time":23064,"text":"I've never enjoyed\na drinks party ever again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25908,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":27790,"text":"And the reason, I only worked out\njust the other day,"},{"time":30910,"text":"which is: when you go\nto a drinks party and you stand up"},{"time":33602,"text":"and hold a glass of red wine\nand you talk endlessly to people,"},{"time":36586,"text":"you don't actually want to spend\nall the time talking."},{"time":39184,"text":"It's really, really tiring."},{"time":40679,"text":"Sometimes you just want to stand there\nsilently, alone with your thoughts."},{"time":44716,"text":"Sometimes you just want to stand\nin the corner and stare out of the window."},{"time":49647,"text":"Now the problem is, when you can't smoke,"},{"time":52845,"text":"if you stand and stare\nout of the window on your own,"},{"time":56520,"text":"you're an antisocial, friendless idiot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58766,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":61100,"text":"If you stand and stare out of the window\non your own with a cigarette,"},{"time":64529,"text":"you're a fucking philosopher."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66306,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":69133,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":74809,"text":"So the power of reframing things"},{"time":79718,"text":"cannot be overstated."},{"time":82198,"text":"What we have is exactly\nthe same thing, the same activity,"},{"time":85594,"text":"but one of them makes you feel great"},{"time":87936,"text":"and the other one,\nwith just a small change of posture,"},{"time":91661,"text":"makes you feel terrible."},{"time":94269,"text":"And I think one of the problems\nwith classical economics is,"},{"time":97198,"text":"it's absolutely preoccupied with reality."},{"time":99655,"text":"And reality isn't a particularly good\nguide to human happiness."},{"time":103895,"text":"Why, for example,\nare pensioners much happier"},{"time":108927,"text":"than the young unemployed?"},{"time":111293,"text":"Both of them, after all,\nare in exactly the same stage of life."},{"time":114563,"text":"You both have too much time\non your hands and not much money."},{"time":118356,"text":"But pensioners are reportedly\nvery, very happy,"},{"time":121081,"text":"whereas the unemployed\nare extraordinarily unhappy and depressed."},{"time":125381,"text":"The reason, I think,\nis that the pensioners believe"},{"time":127855,"text":"they've chosen to be pensioners,"},{"time":129452,"text":"whereas the young unemployed\nfeel it's been thrust upon them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134738,"text":"In England, the upper-middle classes have\nactually solved this problem perfectly,"},{"time":138798,"text":"because they've re-branded unemployment."},{"time":141148,"text":"If you're an upper-middle-class\nEnglish person,"},{"time":143438,"text":"you call unemployment \"a year off.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":145790,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":148508,"text":"And that's because having a son\nwho's unemployed in Manchester"},{"time":151576,"text":"is really quite embarrassing."},{"time":153527,"text":"But having a son\nwho's unemployed in Thailand"},{"time":156629,"text":"is really viewed\nas quite an accomplishment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158736,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":160789,"text":"But actually, the power\nto re-brand things --"},{"time":163136,"text":"to understand that\nour experiences, costs, things"},{"time":168699,"text":"don't actually much depend\non what they really are,"},{"time":171173,"text":"but on how we view them --"},{"time":172770,"text":"I genuinely think can't be overstated."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175703,"text":"There's an experiment\nI think Daniel Pink refers to,"},{"time":178183,"text":"where you put two dogs in a box"},{"time":180726,"text":"and the box has an electric floor."},{"time":185356,"text":"Every now and then,\nan electric shock is applied to the floor,"},{"time":189809,"text":"which pains the dogs."},{"time":192660,"text":"The only difference is one of the dogs\nhas a small button in its half of the box."},{"time":196522,"text":"And when it nuzzles the button,\nthe electric shock stops."},{"time":201376,"text":"The other dog doesn't have the button."},{"time":203904,"text":"It's exposed to exactly the same level\nof pain as the dog in the first box,"},{"time":208169,"text":"but it has no control\nover the circumstances."},{"time":212178,"text":"Generally, the first dog\ncan be relatively content."},{"time":215097,"text":"The second dog lapses\ninto complete depression."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219382,"text":"The circumstances of our lives\nmay actually matter less to our happiness"},{"time":223694,"text":"than the sense of control\nwe feel over our lives."},{"time":228510,"text":"It's an interesting question."},{"time":231269,"text":"We ask the question -- the whole\ndebate in the Western world"},{"time":234371,"text":"is about the level of taxation."},{"time":236229,"text":"But I think there's another\ndebate to be asked,"},{"time":238476,"text":"which is the level of control\nwe have over our tax money,"},{"time":241931,"text":"that what costs us 10 pounds\nin one context can be a curse;"},{"time":246591,"text":"what costs us 10 pounds in a different\ncontext, we may actually welcome."},{"time":252304,"text":"You know, pay 20,000 pounds\nin tax toward health,"},{"time":256642,"text":"and you're merely feeling a mug."},{"time":258595,"text":"Pay 20,000 pounds\nto endow a hospital ward,"},{"time":261881,"text":"and you're called a philanthropist."},{"time":264917,"text":"I'm probably in the wrong country\nto talk about willingness to pay tax."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268342,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":270053,"text":"So I'll give you one in return:\nhow you frame things really matters."},{"time":275277,"text":"Do you call it \"The bailout of Greece\"?"},{"time":277579,"text":"Or \"The bailout of a load of stupid banks\nwhich lent to Greece\"?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":280799,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":281834,"text":"Because they are actually the same thing."},{"time":284208,"text":"What you call them\nactually affects how you react to them,"},{"time":288092,"text":"viscerally and morally."},{"time":290150,"text":"I think psychological value is great,\nto be absolutely honest."},{"time":293368,"text":"One of my great friends,\na professor called Nick Chater,"},{"time":296264,"text":"who's the Professor of Decision\nSciences in London,"},{"time":299162,"text":"believes we should spend far less time\nlooking into humanity's hidden depths,"},{"time":303686,"text":"and spend much more time\nexploring the hidden shallows."},{"time":307133,"text":"I think that's true, actually."},{"time":308669,"text":"I think impressions have an insane effect\non what we think and what we do."},{"time":313767,"text":"But what we don't have is a really\ngood model of human psychology --"},{"time":317374,"text":"at least pre-Kahneman, perhaps,"},{"time":319683,"text":"we didn't have a really good model\nof human psychology"},{"time":322671,"text":"to put alongside models of engineering,\nof neoclassical economics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327568,"text":"So people who believed in psychological\nsolutions didn't have a model."},{"time":330915,"text":"We didn't have a framework."},{"time":332874,"text":"This is what Warren Buffett's\nbusiness partner Charlie Munger calls"},{"time":336245,"text":"\"a latticework on which\nto hang your ideas.\""},{"time":339447,"text":"Engineers, economists,\nclassical economists"},{"time":342344,"text":"all had a very, very robust\nexisting latticework"},{"time":345299,"text":"on which practically\nevery idea could be hung."},{"time":348018,"text":"We merely have a collection\nof random individual insights"},{"time":351438,"text":"without an overall model."},{"time":353612,"text":"And what that means\nis that, in looking at solutions,"},{"time":358075,"text":"we've probably given too much priority"},{"time":360825,"text":"to what I call technical engineering\nsolutions, Newtonian solutions,"},{"time":364970,"text":"and not nearly enough\nto the psychological ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367372,"text":"You know my example of the Eurostar:"},{"time":369709,"text":"six million pounds spent"},{"time":370931,"text":"to reduce the journey time\nbetween Paris and London"},{"time":374175,"text":"by about 40 minutes."},{"time":376569,"text":"For 0.01 percent of this money,\nyou could have put wi-fi on the trains,"},{"time":380441,"text":"which wouldn't have reduced\nthe duration of the journey,"},{"time":383133,"text":"but would have improved its enjoyment\nand its usefulness far more."},{"time":388025,"text":"For maybe 10 percent of the money,"},{"time":389717,"text":"you could have paid all of the world's top\nmale and female supermodels"},{"time":393075,"text":"to walk up and down the train\nhanding out free Château Pétrus"},{"time":396034,"text":"to all the passengers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397332,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":398398,"text":"You'd still have five million\npounds in change,"},{"time":400772,"text":"and people would ask\nfor the trains to be slowed down."}]},{"cues":[{"time":403421,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":407539,"text":"Why were we not given the chance\nto solve that problem psychologically?"},{"time":410925,"text":"I think it's because there's an imbalance,"},{"time":413433,"text":"an asymmetry in the way we treat creative,\nemotionally driven psychological ideas"},{"time":420091,"text":"versus the way we treat rational,\nnumerical, spreadsheet-driven ideas."},{"time":425016,"text":"If you're a creative person,\nI think, quite rightly,"},{"time":427507,"text":"you have to share\nall your ideas for approval"},{"time":429666,"text":"with people much more rational than you."},{"time":431627,"text":"You have to go in\nand have a cost-benefit analysis,"},{"time":434915,"text":"a feasibility study,\nan ROI study and so forth."},{"time":437992,"text":"And I think that's probably right."},{"time":440643,"text":"But this does not apply\nthe other way around."},{"time":443313,"text":"People who have an existing framework --"},{"time":445365,"text":"an economic framework,\nan engineering framework --"},{"time":447768,"text":"feel that, actually,\nlogic is its own answer."},{"time":451503,"text":"What they don't say is,\n\"Well, the numbers all seem to add up,"},{"time":454433,"text":"but before I present this idea,\nI'll show it to some really crazy people"},{"time":457909,"text":"to see if they can come up with\nsomething better.\""},{"time":460299,"text":"And so we -- artificially,\nI think -- prioritize"},{"time":463078,"text":"what I'd call mechanistic ideas\nover psychological ideas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467577,"text":"An example of a great psychological idea:"},{"time":469633,"text":"the single best improvement\nin passenger satisfaction"},{"time":472273,"text":"on the London Underground,"},{"time":473601,"text":"per pound spent,"},{"time":475195,"text":"came when they didn't add\nany extra trains,"},{"time":477554,"text":"nor change the frequency of the trains;"},{"time":479483,"text":"they put dot matrix display boards\non the platforms --"},{"time":483617,"text":"because the nature of a wait is not just\ndependent on its numerical quality,"},{"time":487492,"text":"its duration,"},{"time":488759,"text":"but on the level of uncertainty\nyou experience during that wait."},{"time":492197,"text":"Waiting seven minutes for a train\nwith a countdown clock"},{"time":495110,"text":"is less frustrating and irritating"},{"time":497027,"text":"than waiting four minutes,\nknuckle biting, going,"},{"time":499990,"text":"\"When's this train\ngoing to damn well arrive?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":502879,"text":"Here's a beautiful example\nof a psychological solution"},{"time":505460,"text":"deployed in Korea."},{"time":506655,"text":"Red traffic lights have a countdown delay."},{"time":509088,"text":"It's proven to reduce\nthe accident rate in experiments."},{"time":512138,"text":"Why?"},{"time":513320,"text":"Because road rage, impatience and general\nirritation are massively reduced"},{"time":516865,"text":"when you can actually see\nthe time you have to wait."},{"time":520738,"text":"In China, not really understanding\nthe principle behind this,"},{"time":523665,"text":"they applied the same principle\nto green traffic lights --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":526428,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530290,"text":"which isn't a great idea."},{"time":531836,"text":"You're 200 yards away, you realize\nyou've got five seconds to go,"},{"time":534950,"text":"you floor it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536126,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":539473,"text":"The Koreans, very assiduously,\ndid test both."},{"time":541998,"text":"The accident rate goes down\nwhen you apply this to red traffic lights;"},{"time":545357,"text":"it goes up when you apply it\nto green traffic lights."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547969,"text":"This is all I'm asking for, really,\nin human decision making,"},{"time":550931,"text":"is the consideration\nof these three things."},{"time":553060,"text":"I'm not asking for the complete primacy\nof one over the other."},{"time":556049,"text":"I'm merely saying\nthat when you solve problems,"},{"time":558313,"text":"you should look\nat all three of these equally,"},{"time":560819,"text":"and you should seek as far as possible"},{"time":563044,"text":"to find solutions which sit\nin the sweet spot in the middle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565927,"text":"If you actually look at a great business,"},{"time":567922,"text":"you'll nearly always see all of these\nthree things coming into play."},{"time":571535,"text":"Really successful businesses --"},{"time":573242,"text":"Google is a great, great\ntechnological success,"},{"time":575928,"text":"but it's also based\non a very good psychological insight:"},{"time":580094,"text":"people believe something\nthat only does one thing"},{"time":582675,"text":"is better at that thing than something\nthat does that thing and something else."},{"time":586858,"text":"It's an innate thing\ncalled \"goal dilution.\""},{"time":589588,"text":"Ayelet Fishbach has written\na paper about this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592373,"text":"Everybody else at the time\nof Google, more or less,"},{"time":594887,"text":"was trying to be a portal."},{"time":596158,"text":"Yes, there's a search function,\nbut you also have weather,"},{"time":599008,"text":"sports scores, bits of news."},{"time":601929,"text":"Google understood\nthat if you're just a search engine,"},{"time":604495,"text":"people assume you're a very,\nvery good search engine."},{"time":607357,"text":"All of you know this, actually,\nfrom when you go in to buy a television,"},{"time":610863,"text":"and in the shabbier end\nof the row of flat-screen TVs,"},{"time":613789,"text":"you can see, are these\nrather despised things"},{"time":616118,"text":"called \"combined TV and DVD players.\""},{"time":619802,"text":"And we have no knowledge whatsoever\nof the quality of those things,"},{"time":623017,"text":"but we look at a combined\nTV and DVD player and we go, \"Uck."},{"time":626480,"text":"It's probably a bit of a crap telly\nand a bit rubbish as a DVD player.\""},{"time":630436,"text":"So we walk out of the shops\nwith one of each."},{"time":633326,"text":"Google is as much a psychological success\nas it is a technological one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639000,"text":"I propose that we can use\npsychology to solve problems"},{"time":641657,"text":"that we didn't even realize\nwere problems at all."},{"time":644012,"text":"This is my suggestion for getting people\nto finish their course of antibiotics."},{"time":647799,"text":"Don't give them 24 white pills;"},{"time":649392,"text":"give them 18 white pills and six blue ones"},{"time":652429,"text":"and tell them to take\nthe white pills first,"},{"time":654520,"text":"and then take the blue ones."},{"time":656886,"text":"It's called \"chunking.\""},{"time":658061,"text":"The likelihood that people will get\nto the end is much greater"},{"time":661061,"text":"when there is a milestone\nsomewhere in the middle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":664847,"text":"One of the great mistakes,\nI think, of economics"},{"time":667217,"text":"is it fails to understand\nthat what something is --"},{"time":669644,"text":"whether it's retirement,\nunemployment, cost --"},{"time":673416,"text":"is a function, not only of its amount,\nbut also its meaning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677971,"text":"This is a toll crossing in Britain."},{"time":680797,"text":"Quite often queues happen at the tolls."},{"time":683758,"text":"Sometimes you get very,\nvery severe queues."},{"time":686006,"text":"You could apply\nthe same principle, actually,"},{"time":688220,"text":"to the security lanes in airports."},{"time":689984,"text":"What would happen if you could actually\npay twice as much money"},{"time":692994,"text":"to cross the bridge,"},{"time":694169,"text":"but go through a lane\nthat's an express lane?"},{"time":696312,"text":"It's not an unreasonable thing to do;"},{"time":698106,"text":"it's an economically\nefficient thing to do."},{"time":700141,"text":"Time means more\nto some people than others."},{"time":702206,"text":"If you're waiting trying\nto get to a job interview,"},{"time":704661,"text":"you'd patently pay a couple of pounds more\nto go through the fast lane."},{"time":708899,"text":"If you're on the way\nto visit your mother-in-law,"},{"time":711252,"text":"you'd probably prefer --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":712427,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":713634,"text":"you'd probably prefer to stay on the left."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716356,"text":"The only problem is if you introduce\nthis economically efficient solution,"},{"time":719857,"text":"people hate it ..."},{"time":721634,"text":"because they think you're deliberately\ncreating delays at the bridge"},{"time":724989,"text":"in order to maximize your revenue,"},{"time":726667,"text":"and, \"Why on earth should I pay\nto subsidize your incompetence?\""},{"time":730376,"text":"On the other hand,\nchange the frame slightly"},{"time":732580,"text":"and create charitable yield management,"},{"time":734895,"text":"so the extra money you get\ngoes not to the bridge company,"},{"time":738053,"text":"it goes to charity ..."},{"time":740211,"text":"and the mental willingness\nto pay completely changes."},{"time":744128,"text":"You have a relatively\neconomically efficient solution,"},{"time":746795,"text":"but one that actually meets\nwith public approval"},{"time":749138,"text":"and even a small degree of affection,"},{"time":751162,"text":"rather than being seen as bastardy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754504,"text":"So where economists\nmake the fundamental mistake"},{"time":757182,"text":"is they think that money is money."},{"time":760275,"text":"Actually, my pain experienced\nin paying five pounds"},{"time":764530,"text":"is not just proportionate to the amount,"},{"time":766701,"text":"but where I think that money is going."},{"time":769314,"text":"And I think understanding that\ncould revolutionize tax policy."},{"time":772334,"text":"It could revolutionize\nthe public services."},{"time":774361,"text":"It could actually change things\nquite significantly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":776898,"text":"[Ludwig Von Mises is my hero.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":778384,"text":"Here's a guy you all need to study."},{"time":780122,"text":"He's an Austrian School economist"},{"time":781751,"text":"who was first active in the first half\nof the 20th century in Vienna."},{"time":786339,"text":"What was interesting\nabout the Austrian School"},{"time":788555,"text":"is they actually grew up alongside Freud."},{"time":791612,"text":"And so they're predominantly\ninterested in psychology."},{"time":794289,"text":"They believed that there was\na discipline called praxeology,"},{"time":798866,"text":"which is a prior discipline\nto the study of economics."},{"time":801486,"text":"Praxeology is the study of human choice,\naction and decision-making."},{"time":806660,"text":"I think they're right."},{"time":808009,"text":"I think the danger\nwe have in today's world"},{"time":810101,"text":"is we have the study of economics"},{"time":811805,"text":"considers itself to be a prior discipline\nto the study of human psychology."},{"time":815859,"text":"But as Charlie Munger says,\n\"If economics isn't behavioral,"},{"time":818852,"text":"I don't know what the hell is.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":821804,"text":"Von Mises, interestingly, believes\neconomics is just a subset of psychology."},{"time":827629,"text":"I think he just refers to economics"},{"time":829558,"text":"as \"the study of human praxeology\nunder conditions of scarcity.\""},{"time":833742,"text":"But Von Mises, among many other things,"},{"time":836862,"text":"I think uses an analogy which is probably\nthe best justification and explanation"},{"time":841536,"text":"for the value of marketing,\nthe value of perceived value"},{"time":845767,"text":"and the fact that we should treat it\nas being absolutely equivalent"},{"time":849068,"text":"to any other kind of value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":851054,"text":"We tend to, all of us, even those of us\nwho work in marketing,"},{"time":854030,"text":"think of value in two ways:"},{"time":855352,"text":"the real value, which is when\nyou make something in a factory"},{"time":858273,"text":"or provide a service,"},{"time":859451,"text":"and then there's a dubious value,"},{"time":861093,"text":"which you create by changing\nthe way people look at things."},{"time":863928,"text":"Von Mises completely rejected\nthis distinction."},{"time":866246,"text":"And he used this following analogy:"},{"time":868161,"text":"he referred to strange economists\ncalled the French physiocrats,"},{"time":873518,"text":"who believed that the only true value\nwas what you extracted from the land."},{"time":877172,"text":"So if you're a shepherd\nor a quarryman or a farmer,"},{"time":879681,"text":"you created true value."},{"time":881126,"text":"If however, you bought\nsome wool from the shepherd"},{"time":884009,"text":"and charged a premium\nfor converting it into a hat,"},{"time":887014,"text":"you weren't actually creating value,"},{"time":888820,"text":"you were exploiting the shepherd."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891439,"text":"Now, Von Mises said that modern\neconomists make exactly the same mistake"},{"time":895186,"text":"with regard to advertising and marketing."},{"time":897577,"text":"He says if you run a restaurant,"},{"time":899483,"text":"there is no healthy distinction to be made"},{"time":901746,"text":"between the value you create\nby cooking the food"},{"time":904323,"text":"and the value you create\nby sweeping the floor."},{"time":907203,"text":"One of them creates, perhaps,\nthe primary product --"},{"time":909717,"text":"the thing we think we're paying for --"},{"time":911606,"text":"the other one creates a context\nwithin which we can enjoy"},{"time":914471,"text":"and appreciate that product."},{"time":916019,"text":"And the idea that one of them\nshould have priority over the other"},{"time":919215,"text":"is fundamentally wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":920944,"text":"Try this quick thought experiment:"},{"time":922635,"text":"imagine a restaurant\nthat serves Michelin-starred food,"},{"time":925310,"text":"but where the restaurant smells of sewage"},{"time":927981,"text":"and there's human feces on the floor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":930143,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":931576,"text":"The best thing you can do there\nto create value"},{"time":934093,"text":"is not actually to improve\nthe food still further,"},{"time":937133,"text":"it's to get rid of the smell\nand clean up the floor."},{"time":942259,"text":"And it's vital we understand this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":944836,"text":"If that seems like a sort\nof strange, abstruse thing --"},{"time":947507,"text":"in the UK, the post office\nhad a 98 percent success rate"},{"time":951429,"text":"at delivering first-class\nmail the next day."},{"time":954192,"text":"They decided this wasn't good enough,"},{"time":956101,"text":"and they wanted to get it up to 99."},{"time":959234,"text":"The effort to do that\nalmost broke the organization."},{"time":963520,"text":"If, at the same time,\nyou'd gone and asked people,"},{"time":965934,"text":"\"What percentage of first-class mail\narrives the next day?\""},{"time":968777,"text":"the average answer, or the modal answer,\nwould have been \"50 to 60 percent.\""},{"time":973381,"text":"Now, if your perception\nis much worse than your reality,"},{"time":976119,"text":"what on earth are you doing\ntrying to change the reality?"},{"time":979167,"text":"That's like trying to improve the food\nin a restaurant that stinks."},{"time":984362,"text":"What you need to do is,\nfirst of all, tell people"},{"time":987104,"text":"that 98 percent of first-class mail\ngets there the next day."},{"time":991635,"text":"That's pretty good."},{"time":993180,"text":"I would argue, in Britain,\nthere's a much better frame of reference,"},{"time":996412,"text":"which is to tell people that more\nfirst-class mail arrives the next day"},{"time":999803,"text":"in the UK than in Germany,\nbecause generally, in Britain,"},{"time":1002542,"text":"if you want to make us happy\nabout something,"},{"time":1004850,"text":"just tell us we do it\nbetter than the Germans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007066,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1008820,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1011096,"text":"Choose your frame of reference\nand the perceived value,"},{"time":1014341,"text":"and therefore, the actual value\nis completely transformed."},{"time":1017771,"text":"It has to be said of the Germans"},{"time":1019440,"text":"that the Germans and the French\nare doing a brilliant job"},{"time":1022166,"text":"of creating a united Europe."},{"time":1023644,"text":"The only thing they didn't expect\nis they're uniting Europe"},{"time":1026538,"text":"through a shared mild hatred\nof the French and Germans."},{"time":1029560,"text":"But I'm British;\nthat's the way we like it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031634,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1034099,"text":"What you'll also notice\nis that, in any case,"},{"time":1036244,"text":"our perception is leaky."},{"time":1037458,"text":"We can't tell the difference\nbetween the quality of the food"},{"time":1040360,"text":"and the environment\nin which we consume it."},{"time":1042397,"text":"All of you will have seen this phenomenon"},{"time":1044459,"text":"if you have your car washed or valeted."},{"time":1046465,"text":"When you drive away,\nyour car feels as if it drives better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1049610,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1050975,"text":"And the reason for this --"},{"time":1052255,"text":"unless my car valet\nmysteriously is changing the oil"},{"time":1054927,"text":"and performing work which I'm not paying\nhim for and I'm unaware of --"},{"time":1058294,"text":"is because perception\nis, in any case, leaky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1060625,"text":"Analgesics that are branded\nare more effective at reducing pain"},{"time":1064566,"text":"than analgesics that are not branded."},{"time":1066401,"text":"I don't just mean through reported\npain reduction --"},{"time":1069043,"text":"actual measured pain reduction."},{"time":1070738,"text":"And so perception\nactually is leaky in any case."},{"time":1076021,"text":"So if you do something\nthat's perceptually bad in one respect,"},{"time":1079063,"text":"you can damage the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1080310,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1081485,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}